Notes.Title: Aloalo
Notes.Text:
7Left Path:

Fish to your hearts content, causes the tide to rise and go right

Right: - Took patch of sand (Didn't choose rock)
- Hand over bait - Yes
Kiolled the big fish instead of the x'zomits first, no apparent diff

"We should press on" - Going left - Saved the NPC from dying

"We should press on" - Going left - Ignore NPC...?

Sunny weather, Fire drakes(?)
Rainy weather, Lightning drakes

--------------------------------------------
Center Path:

Killed 4 crawlers on cornacopia, causes it to glow green.
If you kill the tree first, it made a path to the right, we don't know
 if we were standing on it to cause it or not.

We tried killing 1 crawler and then 3 from the last but it didn't light up.
We can try killing 4 with nobody on to see what happens. (Nothing happened)

In the right path, Xyphe hit Lion and she ran after inspecting the tree
Gave us the 8th sticky - Also did not hitting her
-------------------------------------------
Right Path:

Stood up both fallen statues, left first, then right

Asked the faerie to take us to see the secrets

Ignored both fallen statues
Asked the faerie to take us to see the secrets

Can't jump over the whoopie cushions, got all 5 both times we think

Left statue only, declined 3x in a row
Killed big boar > little boars
Picked no chests

On the statues:
O messenger from beyond the horizon, hear me.
Start Whale, clockwise once, counterclockwise once, /thavdance

Start north
O dancer of the skies, hear me.
/blowkiss, Clockwise once, /dance

Start sparrow
O wayfarer of land and sea, hear me.
Sparrow > Whale > Turtlex2, /bow

Did Whale > Turtle > Sparrow statues
Correct is Sparrow > Whale > Turtle
Currently, 3, 5, 7-9
